                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.21/478: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-05T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Confidential. Your 108, August 2, 3 p.m., received early August 5th<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d735fn15">Telegram of Aug. 2 received in the Department’s telegraph
                        office on Aug. 4 at 4.30 p.m., but was not distributed in the Department
                        until the following morning.</note> and immediately communicated to Senator
                    Lodge.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
